cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with computer vision and image processing techniques, specifically non-uniform and multi-illuminant color constancy and shadow detection and removal. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel end-to-end algorithm based on Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential of the proposed approach for joint shadow detection and removal, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the authors mention that they have rendered a large dataset of synthetic images with and without shadows, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
